docs/source/domain-model.md:922:### CDSL Pledge Rules
docs/source/domain-model.md:924:1. Pledgor and pledgee must have BO accounts with CDSL.
docs/source/domain-model.md:925:2. Pledgor submits Pledge Request Form in duplicate to DP.
docs/source/domain-model.md:926:3. Pledgor DP sets pledge request in depository system and PSN is generated.
docs/source/domain-model.md:927:4. Pledgee DP accepts or rejects request.
docs/source/domain-model.md:928:5. Pledge is created after pledgee DP acceptance.
docs/source/domain-model.md:929:6. Loan agreement and disbursement remain outside depository system.
docs/source/domain-model.md:930:7. If default occurs, pledgee may invoke pledge through Invocation Request Form.
docs/source/domain-model.md:931:8. Invocation does not require pledgor confirmation.
docs/source/domain-model.md:932:9. After loan repayment, shares can be unpledged through URF or auto-unpledged by pledgee.
