docs/source/domain-model.md:1137:## 14.3 DefaultCase
docs/source/domain-model.md:1149:### Default Lifecycle
docs/source/domain-model.md:1151:1. Borrower misses scheduled principal repayment.
docs/source/domain-model.md:1152:2. SFPCL provides three-month grace period.
docs/source/domain-model.md:1153:3. If still unpaid, Credit Assessment Team assesses reason.
docs/source/domain-model.md:1154:4. Team classifies non-payment as intentional or non-intentional.
docs/source/domain-model.md:1155:5. If non-intentional, one-year extension is granted.
docs/source/domain-model.md:1156:6. Credit Manager prepares extension note and keeps it in loan file.
docs/source/domain-model.md:1157:7. If still unpaid after one year, loan is scrutinised as not recoverable.
docs/source/domain-model.md:1158:8. Credit Assessment Team prepares Note for Non-Payment.
docs/source/domain-model.md:1159:9. Sanction Committee decides recovery action.
docs/source/domain-model.md:1160:10. Security may be invoked only after approval.
